<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881102-0115 </DOCNO><HL> Damon Creations Closes Sale </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS DNI </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Damon Creations Inc. completed the sale of 85% of its 2.4 million common shares to South China (Jersey) Holdings Ltd., as part of a buy-out agreement.    The indicated value of the shares is more than $6 million.    Damon, a men's-apparel maker here, had agreed to a buy-out by South China, a holding company in Jersey, the Channel Islands, Britain. The merger is expected to be completed by late December.    In connection with the stock sale, Damon said, three of its directors resigned and were succeeded by Richard Lee, who will serve as chairman; Harry Lee, who will be vice chairman; and Donald Young, who will be chief financial officer. </TEXT></DOC>